data.code:
// Generate new token on https://github.com/settings/tokens
// It saves your token locally, so you need not generate new token.
environment.GITHUB_TOKEN = environment.GITHUB_TOKEN || "REPLACE YOUR TOKEN HERE"
await environment.wait()

const options = {
    owner: "sanchezcarlosjr",
    repo: "computer-vision-and-graphics",
    filePath: "assets/evanotebooks/1-server-replication.json",
    commitMessage: "Replicate your changes whatever you want",
    GITHUB_TOKEN: environment.GITHUB_TOKEN
}

editor.blocks.get$.pipe(
  first(),
  map(content =>
    btoa(unescape(encodeURIComponent(JSON.stringify(content, null, 2).replaceAll(options.GITHUB_TOKEN, ""))))),
  commitOnGitHub(options)
)
